Now, having lost 50 lbs myself, I'm creating a company to help people meet their personal goals, no matter how aggressive!

My background is in CS and HCI (CMU undergrad, Stanford grad). I also happen to be an opera singer. I love games and the whole gaming world that comes with it, but I enjoy tons of products outside of gaming as well. I live for working with amazing people on amazing ideas; it's what makes me want to go to work every day.

My high level strategy on creating a good product is to be flexible to accommodate your team on processes, and always aim for a product that is (1) useful, (2) usable, (3) desirable. Also, generating activity and engagement takes priority over generating $ in my head, because you can usually get the latter via the former long-term. Of course, sometimes $ can be a meaningful motivator to reach goals that you would otherwise have less motivation to reach! :)
